{"TopicId":207850,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"Why a Rask and Rusk Infinite Cycler without thrusting would not work (explained using LOGIC!)","CreatedByName":"Akagi","CreatedById":218751,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T16:44:37Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Akagi","CreatedById":218751,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T16:44:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, to get one of those hypothetical Rask-Rusk infinite cyclers, you have to be going just barely fast enough to escape 1, then get a gravity assist off the other to return to the first one, right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, the little bit of speed you would gain with each pass would eventually kick you out of the SOIs, right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, you would have to occasionally retroburn to stay in orbit. You still with me?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid I get something wrong? If I did, please tell me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T17:00:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120184\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650473077\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022218751\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Akagi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, Akagi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, to get one of those hypothetical Rask-Rusk infinite cyclers, you have to be going just barely fast enough to escape 1, then get a gravity assist off the other to return to the first one, right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, the little bit of speed you would gain with each pass would eventually kick you out of the SOIs, right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, you would have to occasionally retroburn to stay in orbit. You still with me?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid I get something wrong? If I did, please tell me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s an unstable system. The most stable orbits either wrap tightly around either Rask or Rusk, or orbit at a distance where Rask and Rusk act like one body.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Akagi","CreatedById":218751,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T17:02:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120194\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650474011\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s an unstable system. The most stable orbits either wrap tightly around either Rask or Rusk, or orbit at a distance where Rask and Rusk act like one body.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*facepalms*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650474173\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022218751\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Akagi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Akagi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u002