 wrong?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Akagi","CreatedById":218751,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T17:14:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120200\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650474532\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat did I do wrong?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, I realized I screwed up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T17:22:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120202\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650474880\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022218751\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Akagi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Akagi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120200\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650474532\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat did I do wrong?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, I realized I screwed up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Akagi","CreatedById":218751,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T17:24:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120203\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650475340\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOrbit would be highly unstable. If Rask and Rusk aren\u0027t tidally locked to their star, I might -- key word being might, I don\u0027t know -- hit the planets as their positions change.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m bad at math ;-;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T17:35:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120204\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650475459\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022218751\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Akagi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Akagi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOrbit would be highly unstable. If Rask and Rusk aren\u0027t tidally locked to their star, I might -- key word being might, I don\u0027t know -- hit the planets as their positions change.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m bad at math ;-;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t worry, I think this pair is going to be a little counterintuitive and treacherous for all of us.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T17:54:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120210\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650476154\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105624\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pthigrivi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, Pthigrivi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t worry, I think this pair is going to be a little counterintuitive and treacherous for all of us.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\na little?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T18:55:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120204\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650475459\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022218751\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Akagi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Akagi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf Rask and Rusk aren\u0027t tidally locked to their star\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat changes if they\u0027re tidally locked? They will be tidally locked to each other, not that their rotational periods would have much relevance to the orbits of spacecraft elsewhere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"t_v","CreatedById":213541,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T19:40:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120243\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650480915\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n46 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat changes if they\u0027re tidally locked? They will be tidally locked to each other, not that their rotational periods would have much relevance to the orbits of spacecraft elsewhere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the two planets were stationary from an inertial reference frame, it would be possible to get a stable orbit around them. But, since they are moving, orbits will be unstable.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-04-20T19:41:19Z\u0022 title=\u002204/20/2022 07:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EApril 20, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by t_v\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nazalassa","CreatedById":217956,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T21:34:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried to simulate a 2-planet-system on my calculator once. Yes, on my \u003Cem\u003Ecalculator\u003C/em\u003E. Worked perfectly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI then tried to simulate Risk and Rusk, explain me why the pair is slowly drifting leftwards on my screen?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI noticed a bug, patched it, and relaunched the simulation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I had 2 bodies orbiting each other. I thought it was stable until they collided and disappeared from the screen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConclusion? Such a system won\u0027t work because of drag, even minimal, due to the void not being completely empty.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr, because of technical limitations. Since there\u0027s no drag implementation on my simulator, I\u0027ll say that physical limitations would render the whole thing unstable if the celestial bodies\u0027 orbits were not burnt into memory.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shdwlrd","CreatedById":113880,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T21:47:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650490444\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217956\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nazalassa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Nazalassa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried to simulate a 2-planet-system on my calculator once. Yes, on my \u003Cem\u003Ecalculator\u003C/em\u003E. Worked perfectly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI then tried to simulate Risk and Rusk, explain me why the pair is slowly drifting leftwards on my screen?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI noticed a bug, patched it, and relaunched the simulation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I had 2 bodies orbiting each other. I thought it was stable until they collided and disappeared from the screen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConclusion? Such a system won\u0027t work because of drag, even minimal, due to the void not being completely empty.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr, because of technical limitations. Since there\u0027s no drag implementation on my simulator, I\u0027ll say that physical limitations would render the whole thing unstable if the celestial bodies\u0027 orbits were not burnt into memory.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s already understood that Rask \u0026amp; Rusk will collide at some point. It\u0027s just being created as a stable system for game play reasons.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nazalassa","CreatedById":217956,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T21:53:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120366\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650491258\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113880\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022shdwlrd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, shdwlrd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s just being created as a stable system for game play reasons.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought KSP2 was meant to be \u003Cem\u003Erealistic\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T21:56:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650491591\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217956\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nazalassa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Nazalassa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120366\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650491258\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113880\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022shdwlrd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, shdwlrd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s just being created as a stable system for game play reasons.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought KSP2 was meant to be \u003Cem\u003Erealistic\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes - strike a balance between realism, simplification for gameplay and realistic dev goals.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nazalassa","CreatedById":217956,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T21:57:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut Rask and Rusk are \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Enot\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E realistic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-20T22:17:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120374\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650491841\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217956\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nazalassa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, Nazalassa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut Rask and Rusk are \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Enot\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E realistic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy not?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shdwlrd","CreatedById":113880,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-21T01:06:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650491591\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217956\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nazalassa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Nazalassa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought KSP2 was meant to be \u003Cem\u003Erealistic\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf Rask \u0026amp; Rusk was truly realistic, how would the player see it? You will have to account for the time it will take players to find and travel to the dancing duel. Not everyone will find it at the same point in the game. Player 1 can take 50 yrs to find and travel there. Player 2 takes 150 yrs, player 3 takes 300 yrs. So you will have to make it stable to account that players will visit the system at different times during their individual play through.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat makes KSP a game, not a simulator. The little annoyances and not quite right things in reality can be ignored for a better experience.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Maria Sirona","CreatedById":210882,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-21T12:42:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650483659\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022213541\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022t_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, t_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the two planets were stationary from an inertial reference frame, it would be possible to get a stable orbit around them. But, since they are moving, orbits will be unstable.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo by your logic getting into Earth oebit is impossible?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-21T12:48:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor folks that have a more intuitive grasp of limited n-body, if I put myself in what looks like a lowish circular equatorial orbit arounds rask, what is going to happen as rusk pulls on my vessel over time?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Maria Sirona","CreatedById":210882,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-21T12:55:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120643\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650545297\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105624\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pthigrivi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Pthigrivi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor folks that have a more intuitive grasp of limited n-body, if I put myself in what looks like a lowish circular equatorial orbit arounds rask, what is going to happen as rusk pulls on my vessel over time?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the orbit will eventually ellipsize (is that even a word) until crashing into Rask\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-21T13:30:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah like, your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E is going to lift perpendicular to the angle to rusk as you\u2019re headed directly away from rusk, and your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E is going to fall on the opposite side of rask as you\u2019re headed directly toward rusk until eventually you crash\u2014right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Maria Sirona","CreatedById":210882,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-21T13:49:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120677\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650547834\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105624\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pthigrivi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, Pthigrivi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah like, your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is going to lift perpendicular to the angle to rusk as you\u2019re headed directly away from rusk, and your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is going to fall on the opposite side of rask as you\u2019re headed directly toward rusk until eventually you crash\u2014right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah if my logic is sound\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-21T14:10:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...And the Akagi and t_v are right that a cycler doing a figure 8 around them wouldn\u0027t work because rask and rusk are proceeding around each other and your incoming vector is going to shift on each orbit.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"t_v","CreatedById":213541,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-21T14:11:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224120635\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650544938\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210882\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Maria Sirona\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Maria Sirona said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo by your logic getting into Earth oebit is impossible?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, earth orbit is actually unstable - in real life, satellites and space stations have to deal with stuff like orbital decay and fluctuations which, if you are in a bad orbit or are really unlucky, can push you into denser atmosphere. Similarly, nothing left in low lunar orbit is thought to survive because the fluctuations caused by Earth\u2019s tug causes orbit altitudes to fluctuate a lot.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}